                    <msContents>
                        <summary>ُThis minute volume contains delicately sprayed stenciled margins
                            throughout. Originally created as a blank book in the mid-17th century,
                            subsequent owners employed it primarily to enter various excerpts of
                            Persian poetry, and several ink drawings. At least three hands entered
                            content, two identifiable. The first, one Muḥammad Ḥusayn, wrote
                            primarily in delicate shikastah script and signed an entry in the month
                            of Muḥarram 1065 AH (Nov. 1654 CE). The second, a Muḥammad Taqī al-Rāzī,
                            wrote primarily in nasta‘līq script and signed one entry in the year
                            1083 AH (1672–1673 CE). </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Hart_21172-item1" n="1">
                            <title key="work_3727">A miscellany of mainly Persian poetry</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa">دلائل الخيرات</title>

                            <author key="person_4302"><persName>Various Authors</persName></author>
                            <editor role="scr ato ins fmo" key=""><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                                    >Muḥammad Ḥusayn, fl. ca. 1654</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد حسين</persName></editor>
                            <editor role="scr ato ins fmo"><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                                    >al-Rāzī, Muḥammad Taqī, fl. ca. 1672–1673</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="ar">محمد تقي الرازي</persName></editor>

                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>

                        </msItem>

                    </msContents>

