                    <history>
                        <origin>Completed as a blank book, probably in <placeName cert="high"
                                type="empire" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/6005089"
                                key="place_6005089">Safavid Empire</placeName>
                            <origDate calendar="#Gregorian" when="1650">ca. 1650 CE</origDate>. </origin>
                        <provenance><p>Subsequently acquired by one Muḥammad Ḥusayn, who signed an
                                entry in the month of Muḥarram 1065 AH (Nov. 1654 CE) and Muḥammad
                                Taqī al-Rāzī, signed another in 1083 AH (1672–1673
                            CE).</p></provenance>
                        <provenance><p>While the circumstances under which this manuscript arrived
                                in Britain remains unclear, collector <persName role="fmo col dno"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77114097" key="person_77114097">Robert
                                    Edward Hart (1878-1946)</persName> acquired them from an
                                unidentified source.</p></provenance>
                        <acquisition><p>Bequeathed to the <orgName role="rpo"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/144365237">Blackburn Museum and Art
                                    Gallery</orgName>, <placeName key="place_7027442"
                                    ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7027442">Blackburn,
                                    Lancashire</placeName>, after the death of <persName
                                    role="fmo col dno" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77114097"
                                    key="person_77114097">Robert Edward Hart (1878-1946)</persName>
                                in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1946"
                            >1946</date>.</p></acquisition>
                    </history>
